WHEREAS, Rex Teixeira and the Association for Frontotemporal Degeneration are
anticipating that greater of awareness of FTD will help make a difference, resulting in more
research, funding, and support for patients and families with hope that a cure can be found; and
WHEREAS, it is important that we help bring greater awareness of this serious disease
to the residents of Tennessee; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Rex Teixeira and the Association for
Frontotemporal Degeneration on their efforts to raise awareness of Frontotemporal
Degeneration in the State of Tennessee.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
